      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos of deep space tonight and it just hit me how much of a joke everything is. like, in a few billion years the sun dies, then the stars go out, and it's just... nothing. every single thing we do, every stupid little struggle, it all just evaporates. it feels like we're just fighting to stay alive in a universe that doesn't even know we're here. what's even the point of carrying on if the end result is just absolute void anyway?",
